 EIGHTEEN persons, including four nursing mothers and their babies have been reported kidnapped in Mando village of Birnin-Gwari Local Govermment Area of Kaduna State. The incident, The Nation gathered, occurred around 1:30am on Wednesday when bandits invaded the village, shooting sporadically. It was also gathered that the bandits went away with four motorcycles and food items. Confirming the incident, Chairman, Birnin-Gwari Emirate Development Union (BEDU), Salisu Haruna, said the bandits struck in the middle of the night. He said the attacked village is about three kilometers away from the Airforce base in Birnin Gwari. Haruna said: “The bandits were heavily armed and went away with 18 people including four nursing mothers and their babies, four motorcycles and plenty of foodstuff.” He said no ransom has been demanded for their freedom and appealed to relevant security agencies to help in their rescue.